    {
      "id": "A1-BG-L02-G2",
      "candidate_type": "lesson",
      "content_form": "grammar_note",
      "learning_role": "structure_grammar",
      "title_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "G2 三大助詞核心地圖",
        "en": "G2 The Three Core Particle Map"
      },
      "summary_i18n": {
        "zh_tw": "用最簡單的方式，記住 은/는, 이/加, 을/를 的核心用途。",
        "en": "Easiest way to remember 은/는, 이/가, and 을/를."
      },
      "payload": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "title_i18n": { "zh_tw": "1. 誰是句子的主角？(은/는 vs 이/가)", "en": "1. Who is the topic/subject?" },
            "explanation_md_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "這兩個最容易搞混。請記住：\n\n- **은/는 (Anchor)**：它是『話題』。用來告訴大家「接下來我要討論這件事」。例如：『(至於) 我呢，我是學生。』\n- **이/가 (Spotlight)**：它是『主語』。用來指定「誰在做這件事」。例如：『誰是學生？』『(是我) **我**才是學生。』",
              "en": "These two are easily confused. Remember:\n\n- **은/는 (Anchor)**: This is the 'Topic'. It tells everyone what we are about to discuss. Example: 'As for me, I am a student.'\n- **이/가 (Spotlight)**: This is the 'Subject'. It points out who specifically is doing the action. Example: 'Who is the student?' 'I (the one) am the student.'"
            }
          },
          {
            "title_i18n": { "zh_tw": "2. 誰被動作打到了？(을/를)", "en": "2. Who is the target? (을/를)" },
            "explanation_md_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "這是最單純的一個。只要前面名詞是動作的『對象』，就加 을/를。\n\n- `밥` ➡️ `밥을 (吃)`\n- `커피` ➡️ `커피를 (喝)`\n- 如果只是單純描述動作，用它就對了。",
              "en": "This is the simplest one. If the noun is the direct target of the action, use 을/를.\n\n- `밥` ➡️ `밥을` (Eat rice)\n- `커피` ➡️ `커피를` (Drink coffee)\n- If you are just describing a simple action, this is the one to use."
            }
          },
          {
            "title_i18n": { "zh_tw": "3. 特別陷阱：저 (我) 碰到 이/가 會變身", "en": "3. Trap: 저 (I) changes with 이/가" },
            "explanation_md_i18n": {
              "zh_tw": "- `저` + `는` ➡️ `저는` (正確)\n- `저` + `가` ➡️ **❌ 저가** (錯誤)\n- `저` + `가` ➡️ **✅ 제가** (一定要變身！)",
              "en": "- `저` + `는` ➡️ `저는` (Correct)\n- `저` + `가` ➡️ **❌ 저가** (Wrong)\n- `저` + `가` ➡️ **✅ 제가** (Special transformation!)"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    },
